<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="101" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,636,2029]" pageId="20" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1823,1848]" pageId="20" pageNumber="101">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[331,538,1823,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Alampyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[331,538,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="101">Alampyris bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Martins &amp; Galileo, 2008" authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2008" box="[697,1100,1823,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Alampyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis box="[697,802,1824,1848]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="101">A. fuscus</emphasis>
Martins &amp; Galileo, 
<number box="[1041,1100,1824,1848]" pageId="20" pageNumber="101" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs as follows: body slender; elytra about 3.0 times as long as length of head + prothorax; elytra without dense pubescence laterally. In 
<emphasis box="[151,259,1896,1920]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="101">
<taxonomicName box="[151,254,1896,1920]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Alampyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscus">A. fuscus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the body is more robust, the elytra is about 
<number box="[746,781,1896,1920]" pageId="20" pageNumber="101" value="2.8">2.8</number>
times as long as head plus prothorax, and has very distinct and dense pubescence laterally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1367,1968,1993]" pageId="20" pageNumber="101" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,636,2029]" box="[199,1367,1968,1993]" pageId="20" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1968,1993]" pageId="20" pageNumber="101">Remarks</emphasis>
. Currently 
<taxonomicName authority="Bates, 1881" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1881" box="[436,690,1968,1993]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Alampyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="101" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[436,551,1968,1993]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="101">Alampyris</emphasis>
Bates, 
<number box="[634,690,1968,1992]" pageId="20" pageNumber="101" value="1881.0">1881</number>
</taxonomicName>
encompasses 
<number box="[850,877,1968,1992]" pageId="20" pageNumber="101" value="11.0">11</number>
species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1034,1119,1968,1993]" name="Mexico" pageId="20" pageNumber="101">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and Central 
<collectingCountry box="[1263,1363,1968,1993]" name="United States of America" pageId="20" pageNumber="101">America</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1007,2004,2029]" pageId="20" pageNumber="101" type="etymology">
